1
00:00:06,350 --> 00:00:08,075
[ Episode 3 ]

2
00:00:27,340 --> 00:00:28,535
Get in.

3
00:00:33,630 --> 00:00:36,065
If not, we'll talk tomorrow
at the school cafeteria.

4
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:10,905
Drop me off at the salon.

5
00:01:13,060 --> 00:01:14,988
You go there too,
so you'll know where it is.

6
00:01:14,989 --> 00:01:16,235
I'm taking you home.

7
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:19,575
So that you can watch me
get scolded by Mother?

8
00:01:20,710 --> 00:01:22,084
It's a pastime of yours, right?

9
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:25,295
You do everything
you're asked to do perfectly

10
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:28,415
and laugh as you watch me fail.

11
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:32,685
Then don't come by anymore.

12
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:38,235
No one in that house
misses you or wants you there.

13
00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:43,024
You have no family.

14
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:49,895
Pull over.

15
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,435
Pull over, darn it!

16
00:02:06,470 --> 00:02:07,665
Thanks.

17
00:02:08,050 --> 00:02:09,955
Thanks for the lift

18
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:12,285
and the advice.

19
00:02:13,290 --> 00:02:14,524
But moreover,

20
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:17,915
thanks for reminding me that
you're a psychopath.

21
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:40,528
[ This is why I hate you. ]

22
00:02:40,529 --> 00:02:43,999
[ Deceiving people while wearing
that fake smile is your specialty. ]

23
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,705
No one in that house
misses you or wants you there.

24
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:49,505
[ You have no family. ]

25
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:06,225
Hey, it's me.

26
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:08,035
Are you free right now?

27
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,535
Let's call the others for a drink.

28
00:03:11,540 --> 00:03:13,665
Of course, I'm buying.

29
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,925
Let me pour you a glass.

30
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:37,775
- Are your glasses filled?
- Of course.

31
00:03:38,029 --> 00:03:40,669
There's no tomorrow,
only a blinding today!

32
00:03:40,670 --> 00:03:42,215
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

33
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,299
- Are you drunk?
- Yes.

34
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,239
- I bet you're not.
- Here.

35
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,915
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

36
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:55,155
He's gone though.

37
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:57,479
He's out of it.

38
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,839
Hey, Jun.

39
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,095
You need to pay for the drinks!

40
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:03,515
He dragged us here saying he'd buy.

41
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:05,315
He already picked up the tab.

42
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,815
This is Jun we're talking about.

43
00:04:08,650 --> 00:04:10,809
He proved his worth once again.

44
00:04:10,810 --> 00:04:11,819
Once again.

45
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:13,709
Guys, I...

46
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:17,155
Life must be so easy for him.

47
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:21,205
He's handsome, popular, and rich.

48
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:24,675
What could possibly worry him?

49
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,615
He should be scolded for having one.

50
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:29,785
Could not worrying
make life boring though?

51
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:33,209
Guys, let's drink to that. Cheers!

52
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:35,145
- Cheers.
- Cheers!

53
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,135
Can you please get up?

54
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:47,075
Take them.

55
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:49,535
That was embarrassing.

56
00:04:54,370 --> 00:04:55,565
What's wrong?

57
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:59,125
It's nothing.

58
00:04:59,910 --> 00:05:01,669
I must've sighed too loudly.

59
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:03,615
Yes, enough for
the whole building to hear.

60
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:05,945
Just let it out.

61
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:08,495
You can consider me as a pretty wall

62
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:10,255
since I won't engage.

63
00:05:11,790 --> 00:05:14,045
I have heaps of research to do

64
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:17,785
and a professor
who only accepts top-notch presentations.

65
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:21,525
I also need to go over a mock Q and A.

66
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,855
Jun's only a freshman,

67
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:27,685
so I don't know if Soo-hyun and I
can handle it all.

68
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:31,245
What if the team members cause trouble?
Will you cover for them

69
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:33,095
as the team leader?

70
00:05:34,850 --> 00:05:37,975
How did he know that they'd cause trouble?

71
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:44,315
[ Soo-hyun ]

72
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:49,589
- Have it on vibrate!
- Why is he calling at this hour?

73
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:50,865
Aren't you going to pick up?

74
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:55,845
Yes, Soo-hyun.

75
00:05:57,770 --> 00:05:59,005
Jun said what?

76
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,555
What's wrong?

77
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,845
I need to step outside for a bit.

78
00:06:07,050 --> 00:06:08,825
Who's calling you out at this hour?

79
00:06:09,030 --> 00:06:10,665
Could he be interested in you?

80
00:06:10,970 --> 00:06:12,075
He's not the type.

81
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:14,585
Either he is or isn't.
Type has nothing to do with it.

82
00:06:15,730 --> 00:06:17,945
He's just wired a little differently.

83
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:20,935
That's how he is.
Anyway, I'll see you later.

84
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:25,685
Don't make a sound.
You'd better not wake me up!

85
00:07:06,290 --> 00:07:07,575
Jun?

86
00:07:12,930 --> 00:07:14,475
So-bin, it's you.

87
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:17,335
How did you know I was here?

88
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:19,365
Soo-hyun said you'd be here.

89
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,705
You guys must be close.

90
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,305
Except me...

91
00:07:25,430 --> 00:07:27,719
Are you okay? How much did you drink?

92
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,435
Not much...

93
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:33,085
I can drink more.

94
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,605
Let's go drink more...

95
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:43,565
What's wrong? Can you pull yourself up?

96
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:01,385
So-bin.

97
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:04,545
Can you please like me?

98
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:17,305
Why won't you answer?

99
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:20,215
Don't you like me?

100
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:26,195
So you hate me too.

101
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:30,595
It's not that I hate you.

102
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,665
Right?

103
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,275
I knew you of all people would like me.

104
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:40,454
I knew you'd like me.

105
00:08:41,849 --> 00:08:43,225
Actually,

106
00:08:44,839 --> 00:08:47,054
I like someone else.

107
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,215
What?

108
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:53,655
There's someone else I like.

109
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:55,935
What?

110
00:08:57,780 --> 00:09:01,265
I can't like you
because I have feelings for someone else!

111
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:07,809
Jun, can you get a grip on yourself?

112
00:09:07,810 --> 00:09:09,715
Jun, are you asleep?

113
00:09:10,140 --> 00:09:12,525
- Hey.
- Is he asleep?

114
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,725
Soo-hyun?

115
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:16,795
Give him to me.

116
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,725
Sure.

117
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,825
Do you know where he lives?

118
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,425
What? I don't.

119
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:33,465
I think Hye-ji knows though.

120
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,555
Oh, no.

121
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:42,925
Could he have heard what I said?

122
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:53,750
[ Youth Villa ]

123
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:49,705
This seems to be the place.

124
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,705
Oh, no.

125
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,689
Unbelievable.

126
00:10:03,690 --> 00:10:05,765
We're almost there.

127
00:10:14,730 --> 00:10:17,899
Jun, what's your door lock combination?

128
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,095
Jun?

129
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:21,515
I've done enough.

130
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:23,145
Just a second.

131
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:25,035
It's a biometric lock.

132
00:10:26,660 --> 00:10:30,445
Could you bend down a little?

133
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,395
A little closer.

134
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,345
Could you lift him up slightly?

135
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,075
Darn it.

136
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:47,785
Darn these fingers. Work with me!

137
00:10:49,930 --> 00:10:52,135
Yes! That's a good boy.

138
00:10:57,940 --> 00:11:00,145
It worked! Soo-hyun, hurry inside.

139
00:11:09,330 --> 00:11:10,965
You must be exhausted.

140
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,075
Your jacket.

141
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:20,255
- Please take it off and I'll--
- Why should you?

142
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,085
You're right.

143
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:27,335
I probably earned the right
to use the bathroom.

144
00:11:29,050 --> 00:11:32,445
Same here. I probably earned the right
to get a glass of water.

145
00:12:40,980 --> 00:12:42,225
What is it?

146
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,205
Nothing.

147
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:47,155
- The cup's overflowing.
- My gosh!

148
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,475
Would you like some water?

149
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,995
[ Did he hear what I said or didn't he? ]

150
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,885
[ Should I ask? ]

151
00:13:11,210 --> 00:13:12,495
Thanks.

152
00:13:13,010 --> 00:13:15,135
Soo-hyun, wait.

153
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,945
Did you perhaps hear

154
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:24,105
what I said earlier?

155
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,129
I mean,

156
00:13:30,130 --> 00:13:33,739
I hope you heard me
thanking you for carrying him here.

157
00:13:33,740 --> 00:13:36,425
It was exhausting for you too.
We should go.

158
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,245
Sure.

159
00:13:47,330 --> 00:13:49,365
Doesn't something seem to be up with him?

160
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,575
I really think something's up.

161
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:54,815
So-bin.

162
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:57,595
Can you please like me?

163
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,915
He's liked by everyone, so why me?

164
00:14:04,230 --> 00:14:05,549
Is something troubling him?

165
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:07,185
Your mind's running off to places again.

166
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,525
Yours don't though.

167
00:14:11,050 --> 00:14:12,685
Because I don't care about others.

168
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,755
As if.

169
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:18,405
After getting his call,
you sent me looking for him.

170
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:21,429
Then you came by and carried him home

171
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:23,285
to his house.

172
00:14:23,810 --> 00:14:25,705
I call that caring.

173
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,325
I talk a lot, don't I?

174
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:35,035
I didn't want his last call
to be have been to me

175
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,885
which is why I called you.

176
00:14:37,930 --> 00:14:39,305
I followed you there though

177
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:43,135
because I didn't want to put you out
more than necessary.

178
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:47,795
Right. If you hadn't shown up,

179
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:50,525
we would've stayed there all night.

180
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:52,325
Anyway, you did good.

181
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:56,985
- This is where we ended up.
- Good night.

182
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,985
Did you purposely walk me back?

183
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:04,419
I'd rather you not tell Jun that I came.

184
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:05,649
Why not?

185
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:08,035
My curiosity is at it again.

186
00:15:08,770 --> 00:15:11,335
I'm sure you have your reasons.
Your secret's safe with me.

187
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:16,215
I just don't want him to get clingy
in the name of trying to thank me.

188
00:15:17,970 --> 00:15:19,475
Jun's like that, isn't he?

189
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:22,775
Good night then.

190
00:15:29,850 --> 00:15:32,145
You think you know him,
but then you don't.

191
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:35,575
Darn it. Whatever.

192
00:15:37,330 --> 00:15:40,325
[ Youth Villa ]

193
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:28,855
Did someone

194
00:16:30,130 --> 00:16:31,855
bring me home last night?

195
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:42,805
Darn it. What on earth happened?

196
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,005
Short black hair.

197
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:05,505
Whose is it?

198
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:11,625
- So-bin!
- Hey, Jun.

199
00:17:12,149 --> 00:17:14,665
- Are you all right?
- What about you?

200
00:17:15,710 --> 00:17:18,315
Me? Why would you ask?

201
00:17:19,190 --> 00:17:21,085
I doubt it happened,

202
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,825
but did I make
some kind of mistake last night?

203
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:28,429
Can you please like me?

204
00:17:28,430 --> 00:17:31,464
I can't like you
because I have feelings for someone else!

205
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:38,189
Did you make any mistakes? Yes, you did.

206
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:39,875
Not to me, but to...

207
00:17:43,780 --> 00:17:45,155
I mean...

208
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:49,995
You! How could you get wasted like that?

209
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:53,465
That's the mistake you made.
A colossal mistake!

210
00:17:56,630 --> 00:17:58,655
I'm busy and must hang up.

211
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:04,859
What was that about?

212
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:09,999
[ Calls ]

213
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,245
[ Yesterday, Nam Soo-hyun ]

214
00:18:14,180 --> 00:18:15,645
I called Nam Soo-hyun.

215
00:18:18,670 --> 00:18:20,615
I really did make a mistake.

216
00:18:29,940 --> 00:18:31,965
Did he completely blackout?

217
00:18:32,180 --> 00:18:34,075
You're mumbling by yourself again.

218
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,999
- Did I?
- It'll lead to a mishap one day.

219
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,645
You'll blurt out your feelings
without realizing it.

220
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:43,665
That's a horror story.

221
00:18:43,970 --> 00:18:46,005
What's a horror is your face!

222
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:49,475
- Unbelievable.
- Did you drink last night?

223
00:18:49,870 --> 00:18:51,009
No.

224
00:18:51,010 --> 00:18:54,179
I took care of a drunken imbecile.

225
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:55,375
You did what?

226
00:18:55,540 --> 00:18:57,519
Who had the audacity to make you do that?

227
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,115
Was it that roommate of yours?

228
00:18:59,770 --> 00:19:01,699
Says the actual troublemaker.

229
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,809
I spent my teens taking care of you.

230
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:05,055
Right.

231
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:08,169
Since that's the case, I'll compensate you

232
00:19:08,170 --> 00:19:09,839
for your devotion of youth.

233
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,695
- With what?
- Fried chicken and beer!

234
00:19:12,350 --> 00:19:14,115
- Have it yourself.
- Sure.

235
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:18,645
- Be good to me while I'm still here.
- You'll always be here, for sure.

236
00:19:19,610 --> 00:19:22,525
- No one can guarantee that.
- Are you going somewhere?

237
00:19:25,730 --> 00:19:27,619
What's scarier is

238
00:19:27,620 --> 00:19:29,255
our friendship drifting apart.

239
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,689
Even being physically close
can't remedy that.

240
00:19:33,690 --> 00:19:35,105
Why would we grow distant?

241
00:19:36,420 --> 00:19:37,615
I'm off.

242
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:40,555
What? Hey, don't go.

243
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:42,715
Don't put space between us!

244
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:46,675
Is it the spring blues?

245
00:20:32,730 --> 00:20:33,925
Professor Yeo.

246
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:39,605
Isn't your younger brother
a freshman in the department?

247
00:20:41,620 --> 00:20:42,905
Why do you ask?

248
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,565
Well, I just thought
I would personally look out for him.

249
00:20:48,270 --> 00:20:50,605
Please don't. That's hardly necessary.

250
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,905
Audacious, aren't you?

251
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:09,485
- Sorry?
- You're already flirting your way through.

252
00:21:12,250 --> 00:21:13,789
I don't quite follow.

253
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:16,419
You got this position
by currying favors with Yeo Jun.

254
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:19,059
I thought it was weird for him

255
00:21:19,060 --> 00:21:20,305
to turn down my offer.

256
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:24,519
Jun willingly gave up his spot--

257
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:25,675
He gave it up?

258
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:27,825
This seems like nothing, doesn't it?

259
00:21:28,660 --> 00:21:31,395
You think I'm being petty
over a research gig.

260
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,235
One incident can tell you a lot.

261
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:36,715
I'm sorry.

262
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:39,959
This wasn't my spot to begin with.

263
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,835
Why do you say that?
Are you going to quit?

264
00:21:44,230 --> 00:21:47,805
Because if you do, it'll seem like
I got cranky and fired you.

265
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,915
How did you get Ms. Seol
on your side anyway?

266
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:56,335
You must be a talented one.

267
00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:17,670
[ Yeo Jun ]

268
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:13,929
[ - Five, four ]
- Five, four

269
00:22:13,930 --> 00:22:16,705
[ - three, two... ]
- two.

270
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:18,465
One!

271
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:24,275
- Hey, Jun.
